  <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does BUPA's pre-existing condition coverage work?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        BUPA uses medical underwriting—they review your health history during application. Well-controlled conditions are often covered from day one. Some conditions may have waiting periods or premium loadings. Unlike moratorium underwriting, you get clarity upfront about what's covered rather than waiting 2 years to find out.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What does "mental health parity" actually guarantee?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        BUPA's mental health parity means mental health conditions are covered under the same terms as physical health—same coverage limits, same access, same network. There are no separate "mental health maximums" or session limits that many insurers impose. If your plan covers $2M in physical health care, it covers $2M in mental health care.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I upgrade from IMG to BUPA later?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes, but conditions that develop while on IMG become pre-existing conditions for BUPA. If you develop depression on IMG (which may not cover it) and want to switch to BUPA, that depression would be subject to BUPA's underwriting process. Consider your long-term health trajectory when choosing.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does BUPA's no-claims discount work?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        BUPA rewards claim-free years with premium discounts. The exact discount varies but can reach 10–20% off your renewal premium after several claim-free years. This makes BUPA increasingly cost-effective for healthy members over time, partially offsetting their higher base premiums.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is IMG Global reliable for large claims?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        IMG Global's 4.6/5 Trustpilot rating suggests strong claims satisfaction. Customers report reliable payment even for significant claims. The budget pricing doesn't mean they avoid paying—it means they limit what's covered (mental health, maternity, pre-existing conditions) to keep costs down while reliably covering what's included.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What if I need US care with IMG Global?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        IMG Global covers US care, but the 50% deductible waiver doesn't apply. You pay your full deductible for US care. If you have a $10,000 deductible, that's $10,000 out-of-pocket before coverage starts for US treatment (versus $5,000 for international care). Plan accordingly if you spend time in the US.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

